==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from Italian ''legato'', past participle of ''legare'', meaning "to tie", "to tie up", "to tie together", or "to bind", learned borrowing from Latin ''ligare''.

===Pronunciation===
Syllables: le·ga·to
<br>[[AHD]]: lə·gäʹtō
<br>[[IPA]]: ləˈɡɑ.tʊ
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑːtəʊ|-ɑːtəʊ]]

===Adverb===
'''legato'''

#{{music}} Smoothly, in a connected manner.  Smoothly connected.
#:''Play '''legato''' not portato.''
#A slur curve above or below the notes indicating that they should be played legato.

====Antonym====
*[[staccato]]

